                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/842: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-31T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 31, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 1, 1944—10:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2122. In conversation with the Minister for Foreign Affairs last night
                    (Department’s 792, September 30, Embassy’s 1806, November 4, Department’s 980,
                    December 28 [<hi rend="italic">29</hi>])<note n="1" xml:id="d1181fn1">Telegrams
                        No. 1806 and No. 980 not printed; in telegram No. 980 (867.24/807) the
                        Department had requested the Ambassador to ascertain the Turkish reaction to
                        the proposal advanced in telegram No. 792.</note> I urged him to expedite
                    his reply to our most recent proposal in connection with the master Lend-Lease
                    agreement and stressed the desirability of concluding the agreement as soon as
                    possible. Numan said he had been delayed in making his reply to us by a desire
                    to study the British proposals in connection with our agreement. He added that
                    he expected to be in a position shortly after the first of the year to conclude
                    an agreement with us and indicated that he did not anticipate any
                    difficulties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
